64 plan of the city or county also be a basis for the preparation of the capital
65 improvement plan. Section 9 also requires that the master plan be the basis for
66 zoning ordinances and regulations.
67 Existing law authorizes a governing body to divide the city, county or region
68 into zoning districts of such number, shape and area as are best suited to carry out
69 certain purposes. Within a zoning district, the governing body may regulate and
70 restrict the erection, construction, reconstruction, alteration, repair or use of
71 buildings, structures or land. Zoning regulations must be adopted in accordance
72 with the master plan for land use. (NRS 278.250) Section 10 of this bill requires
73 instead that the zoning regulations be consistent with the master plan for land use.
74 Section 11 of this bill requires the governing body or planning commission of
75 the city, county or region to consider conformity with the zoning ordinances and
76 master plan when taking final action on a tentative map.
77 Existing law sets forth certain procedures and requirements relating to the
78 adoption of the master plan, any part of the master plan or any substantial
79 amendment thereof by the commission. (NRS 278.210) Section 8 of this bill adds a
80 requirement that, in counties whose population is 700,000 or more, before the
81 commission may review or adopt any proposed amendment to a land use element of
82 a master plan, the proposed amendment first must be submitted to the staff of the
83 city or county to make a recommendation for approval or denial and establishes the
84 criteria upon which the recommendation must be made.
